{"key":"processedPost-9061138","value":{"id":9061138,"first":9060361,"last":9063315,"when":1223699732,"utime":"10/11/08 07:35 AM","content":"I was actually going to make a similar heater for my doghouse, since we now live in an extremely cold high elevation mountain climate.&nbsp; It's getting down to 10F tonight, and was 14F last night, two weeks before Halloween.&nbsp; I decided to let her tough it out and grow a winter coat instead.<br /><br />One suggestion I'd make if your house is super cold.&nbsp; Ground the coffee can so that if the wires short out to it, the breaker will trip.&nbsp; Without a ground connection, if the hot wire shorts to the can and you touch it, you'll get knocked on your ass.&nbsp; I noticed you're using two wire cords.&nbsp; Get a three wire supply cord and connect the green to the coffee can for safety.<br />RR","title":"Re: Lightbulb Heater Incubator"}}